title: For Sale:  Intermediate Pistol Course on Sunday June 8th 2014
postcontent:
Prerequisites: NRA Basic Pistol or equivalent
The Intermediate Pistol Course is all about getting comfortable with your firearm.  This course will drive the core marksmanship fundamentals required to master the manipulation of your firearm.  This course will take you out of the comfortable static shooting most people do at the local range.  Emphasis is taken on instilling safety and proficiency with your firearm.
This course will prepare you to properly, safely and effectively unholster your firearm and present it to a threat if such need should arise.  The dynamics of shooting at closer distances will be explained and the hands-on drills will drive home the importance of the core fundamentals.
This course is 25% classroom and 75% hands-on and will have you firing your handgun for approximately 6 hours.  Manipulating your firearm under new pressures and timed constraints will prepare you for the unexpected.  This course will not only teach you the skills, but will also give you the confidence you need to feel comfortable handling your firearm in worst case scenarios.  This course is 1 day of hands-on lecture and hands-on drills.

title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Classes $75
postcontent:
The class is the NRA Basic Pistol / FL Concealed Weapons Permit class.  It covers safety, hands on classroom training, live fire training at the range, personal gun selection, cleaning/caring for a firearm and the laws/rules/procedures for the FL Concealed Weapons Permit. I also have a section of the class dedicated to personal defense with a firearm.  It is not necessary to own a firearm to attend the class as I have demo models.  If you own a firearm I recommend you bring it to class so you can train with it.  We typically spend 3 to 3 1/2 hours in the classroom and about an hour on the range. Once you complete the class you will receive a certificate that satisfies the requirements for the FL CWP.  You then fill out an application, have your fingerprints and picture taken and submit the application.  The cost of the actual permit is $70 and the fingerprint / back round check is $42.  The permit is good for 7 years.  I hold the public classes in the conference rooms at Homewood Suites by Pensacola Airport (or your location for a private class of 4 or more students).  The class is $75 per student and may be paid in cash, money order or local check.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Beautiful 21' Four Winns Liberator with 460 big block
postcontent:
had a deal fall through so the boat is still available.
 This is a turn key water ready boat with no issues.   
I have for sale a unique boat that is in excellent shape and has been updated with tons of extras,
to start with it is an 1988 Four Winns Liberator 211 it has a very healthy big block 460 Ford engine with Cobra outdrive.  The motor runs great has a choppy idle and a ton of power (low 60s on gps) the entire boat was checked out at the beginning of May and received a clean bill of health from an actual Marine mechanic, the only issue was 1 of the 2 batteries was not keeping a charge ( I have since replaced both batteries with new deep cell marine batteries)  the batteries both run through a switch which allows you to choose between battery 1 or 2 or both so that you wont have a dead battery after listening to the stereo for hours and can charge both when boat is running.  I replaced the head unit with a Jensen marine unit that has both aux/usp jacks as well as CD and radio functions, the radio is played through new kenwood Marine speakers and sounds great ( it is wired for a sub and has an amp but I have not messed with that just mids and highs).  Both seats up front have been redone with the last 2 years as was the sun deck that covers the engine, it has a canopy that I never messed with.  The boat is a cuddy cabin that is an open style cuddy no bathroom or sink, everything is in good shape and it can fit several people comfortably.  I received maintenance records for the last 13 years from the previous owner and it was always stored inside. The boat is in fantastic shape and you will not see many of these running around the lake, and not one this nice.  The whole exhaust was redone last year and a baffle was placed in the exhaust to quiet it down a bit.  I have left over tubing to put in place of the baffle if you want it louder.
  The trailer is near new and was completely restored 2 years ago and updated with new everything, winch, jack, toolbox, and all wiring.  Updated with all LEDs and was sandblasted and repainted with original graphics, brakes were all redone and updated surge brakes along with trailer brakes were all redone. It is an easy load trailer.
        I have titles to both the boat and trailer, I also have a list of extras that come with the package price including; 2 newer tubes, ropes, anchors, a 2nd Stainless Steel Turbo prop, a very nice Garmin marine unit with satellite gps and depth finder, life jackets, and I'm sure I'm forgetting some things.  Feel free to call/text with questions REDACTED my name is Steve I'm asking $9,800 (its insured for 12,500 and books out higher without the list of extras)  or best offer I'd also be open to trades plus cash( high end firearms only I'm not looking for a bunch of handguns or AKs plus cash) , I have a short video of the boat running and it has been on the water once this year with no issues. Thanks

title: For Sale:  Utah and Oregon Concealed Carry Class 6/2/2014
postcontent:
Utah and Oregon Concealed Carry Class

Monday, June 2, 2014 7:00 PM

Honey Toast Cafe, 12520 SW Farmington Road, Beaverton, OR 97005

Class cost is $65. Save $5 by pre-registering online!

Pre-Register Online: http://www.keepcalmandcarry.net/utah-and-oregon-concealed-carry-class-2-6-2014-Registration

This class covers everything you need to get your Oregon Concealed Handgun License and your Utah Concealed Firearms Permit. 

Our course exceeds all firearms safety training exceeds the requirements to obtain your Utah CFP, pursuant to Utah Code Title 53 Chapter 5 Section 704, and your Oregon CHL pursuant to ORS 166.291(f)(G). 

Our process starts with issuing you a packet of information, an application for your permit, and fingerprint cards that you will need. We will do your fingerprinting, take your passport photo and make copies of your driver's license before class starts. We do this so that upon completion of this class, you will have a complete packet which you can submit to Utah BCI (Bureau of Criminal Identification) with your payment. You will also have all the information you need to obtain your Oregon CHL from your local Sheriff's department. 

Subjects covered are: Basic Handgun Safety, Tactical Issues, Concealed Carry Firearm selection tips, Ammunition, Holsters, Gun Free Zones, Reciprocity, Cleaning, Storage, Firearm Transport, Justifiable Force, Criminal and Civil liability, How to interact with Law Enforcement, and how to apply for your Permit. 

After attending this class you will have a fundamental understanding about handgun safety and the rights and responsibilities and laws associated with the carrying of a concealed Handgun in multiple states. 

This is NOT a live firing class. Do NOT bring a firearm with you to the class. 

Even though the class time is only scheduled to be 2 1/2 hours long, there will be time for questions and answers after the class. 

More Information: http://www.keepcalmandcarry.net/utah-and-oregon-concealed-carry-class-2-6-2014-Schedule 
 Download a Flyer: http://www.keepcalmandcarry.net/ClassFlyer/utah-and-oregon-concealed-carry-class-6-2-2014.pdf
